question: Emmett Shear still CEO of OpenAI by end of week?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if Emmett Shear remains in the official position of CEO of OpenAI through Nov 26, 2023, 11:59 PM ET. 

The market will resolve to "No" if Emmett Shear has stepped down, been replaced, or otherwise ceased holding the position of CEO at OpenAI before the end of this week. 

Resolution will be based on official OpenAI announcements or a consensus of credible media reporting.

question: OpenAI board out by end of week?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if all current board members of OpenAI as of Nov 19 (Ilya Sutskever, Adam D'Angelo, Helen Toner, Tasha McCauley) resign or are replaced from their positions by Nov 26, 11:59 PM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No."

Resignation refers to officially stepping down from their positions, and must be confirmed by official OpenAI communication or credible news sources.

question: Will Linda Yaccarino remain CEO of X through 2023?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if Linda Yaccarino remains CEO of X from the date of this market's inception, November 20, through December 31, 2023, 11:59 PM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

An announcement that Linda Yaccarino will no longer be CEO on or before December 31 will not be sufficient to resolve this market. Only confirmation that Linda Yaccarino is no longer CEO of X within the market timeframe will result in this market resolving to "No".

This market's primary resolution source will be official information from X and/or Yaccarino, however a consensus of credible reporting sources will also be used.

question: Over 500 OpenAI resignations this week?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if there are over 500 confirmed employee resignations from OpenAI by Nov 24, 11:59 PM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No." A resignation is defined as a voluntary departure from a current position within the organization.

Confirmation must come from official OpenAI announcements, credible news reporting, or direct statements from the individuals involved. This market may stay open past the deadline until is unambiguous as to whether the number of resignations before the end date was over/under 500.
